    public class RegularAtom
extends java.lang.Object
implements Atom
    An Atom is the physical instance of an atom in three dimensional space. This is the smallest entity representable in a LeafSubstructure.

      • RegularAtom

        public RegularAtom(Atom atom)
        This is a copy constructor. Creates a new atom with the same attributes as the given atom. The neighbours of this atom are NOT copied. Due to the nature of this operation it would be bad to keep a part of the relations to the lifecycle of the atom to copy. If you want to keep the neighbouring atoms, copy the superordinate substructure that contains this atom and it will also traverse and copy the neighbouring atoms.
        Parameters:
        atom - The atom to copy.
